Gluttony

Passive Ability

When facing nearby Berries, increases movement speed by 25%.

Doubles the HP restored from eating Sitrus Berries. Restores an additional 1% max HP + 0 x (Lv. - 1) + 23 HP from eating Oran Berries (from Greedent Cheek Pouch).

Attack

Auto Attack

Becomes a boosted attack with every third attack, belly flopping forward to deal increased damage to opposing Pokémon and decrease their movement speed by 20% for 1s when it hits.

100% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 0

86% Atk + 9 x (Level - 1) + 170

Tackle

Move 1

6.00s Dash

The user readies a boosted attack and dashes belly first forward, damaging opposing Pokémon and shoving the first opposing Pokémon hit for 1s. The boosted attack from this move remains readied until used.

211% Atk + 23 x (Level - 1) + 420

Tackle Upgrade Choices

Heavy Slam

6.00s Dash

The user jumps up and slams down at the designated location, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect and throwing them for 1s.

200% Atk + 15 x (Level - 1) + 400

Increases the damage of this move.

262% Atk + 21 x (Level - 1) + 520

Flail

6.50s Buff

The user increases their movement speed by 80% for 3s (decaying by 10% every 0.5s over 2s; minimum 40% for 1s before this buff ends) and decreases the movement speed of nearby opposing Pokémon by 50% for 1.5s, and starts flailing about for 5s.

While flailing about, auto attacks deal increased damage, with damage strengthening for every 20% max HP the user is missing. Basic attacks used while flailing about also decrease the movement speed of opposing Pokémon hit by 20% for 1s; boosted attacks decrease movement speed by 50% for 1s.

45% Atk  +  7 x (Level - 1)  +  90 + 5% Max HP

Against Wild Pokemon: The total damage is capped at 2000.

67.5% Atk  +  10 x (Level - 1)  +  135 + 6% Max HP

Against Wild Pokemon: The total damage is capped at 2500.

Increases the damage dealt by auto attacks used while flailing about.

When the user is below 40% max HP, auto attacks also restore the user's HP for 30% of damage dealt.

81% Atk  +  7 x (Level - 1)  +  100 + 5% Max HP

121.5% Atk  +  10 x (Level - 1)  +  150 + 6% Max HP

Rest

Move 2

10.00s Recovery

The user becomes unstoppable and falls asleep on the spot for 3s, restoring 8% max HP every 1s over 3s (maximum 24% max HP). While using this move, opposing Pokémon cannot pass through Snorlax.

This move cannot be used within an opposing Miraidon's Electric Terrain.

Rest Upgrade Choices

Block

8.00s Hindrance

The user gains a shield for 3.5s; becomes unstoppable, decreases their movement speed by 30% and creates a wall with their arms spread wide in the designated direction for up to 4s. Opposing Pokémon cannot pass through the wall from behind, and those that contact the wall from the front are shoved and stunned for 0.45s; targets cannot be shoved more than once every 1s (maximum 4 times).

The user can use this move again to drop the wall early, becoming vulnerable to hindrances and returning to normal movement speed.

Increases the user's Defense and Sp. Def by 35% while holding up the wall. Shoves opposing Pokémon contacting the wall from the front not more than once every 0.5s (maximum 8 times).

Yawn

10.50s Hindrance

The user lets out a huge yawn in the designated direction, putting opposing Pokémon in the area of effect to a deep sleep for up to 3s.

Targets that are hit after their deep sleep is halfway through wake up immediately.

Decreases the movement speed of opposing Pokémon waking up from a full deep sleep by 35% for 3s.

Power Nap

Unite Move

89s 80000 Recovery

Unlocks at level 9

The user becomes unstoppable and slams onto their back fast asleep, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect and throwing them for 0.6s; then continues to sleep for up to 4s afterward. The user starts snoring for the remainder of the Unite Move, restoring 10% max HP over time while fast asleep (up to 9 times; maximum 90%), damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect with a huge snore every 1.5s and decreasing their movement speed by 30% for 1s when hit. This Unite Move can be used again before the user snores a second time to flip over in the designated sideways direction and slam the ground, dealing an extra instance of snore damage in the area of effect and throwing opposing Pokémon hit for 1s. While the user is fast asleep, opposing Pokémon cannot pass through Snorlax.

After the user flips over or snores a second time, the user can use this Unite Move again to stop sleeping early, becoming vulnerable to hindrances and returning to normal.

132% Atk + 8 x (Level - 1) + 360

Deals 50% of the initial damage, 3 times.
66% Atk + 4 x (Level - 1) + 180

Unite Buffs (6s duration):

30% Movement Speed, 40% Max HP Shield
